%h2 The Bipolar Cycle

%p There are four cycles: Yearly, Monthly, Weekly, and Daily.

%p Each cycle can be split into two halves: Up (the high half of the cycle) and Down (the low half of the cycle).

%ul.none
  %li <b>Yearly:</b> Six months up, Six months down (with about two weeks off)
  %li <b>Monthly:</b> Two weeks up, Two weeks down (with about three days off)
  %li <b>Weekly:</b> Three days up, Three days down (with about one day off)
  %li <b>Daily:</b> Eight hours up, Eight hours down (with about eight hours off)

%p These cycles are additive: you are Manic (highest) when all four cycles are Up at the same time and you are Depressed (lowest) when all four cycles are Down at the same time.

%p Each bipolar cycle can also be split into two halves based on the off times when the cycle resets: Early (the first half of the cycle which is centered around energy) and Late (the second half of the cycle which is centered around strength).

%p Each cycle can be entrained to run a little faster or shorter or have a little more or less off time. If your cycles have been entrained to the clock and calendar and are reset at common times off for each cycle, you get the following:

